-- Yuan Gains on Speculation China Will Allow Appreciation Before G-20 Meets
-- Bob Chen
-- 2010-06-24T09:25:36Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-24/yuan-gains-on-speculation-china-will-allow-appreciation-before-g-20-meets.html

          
          
             The yuan climbed toward its
strongest level since 1993 on speculation the central bank will
allow the currency to appreciate before the Group of 20 meeting
this weekend.  
 The yuan strengthened 0.17 percent to 6.8005 per dollar,
after reaching 6.79 on June 22.  
